Feeld (previously called 3nder) is a location-based social discovery service application for iOS and Android that facilitates communication between people interested in polyamory, kink, and alternative sexual preferences such as more than one partner at once. 3nder was launched in the UK in July 2014 and in the US in 2015. As of August 1, 2016, it had had over 1.6M downloads on iOS. A major update to the interface was released December 2017.
Feeld is developed by Feeld Ltd., a London-based startup company founded in 2014 by Bulgarian-born designer Dimo Trifonov.
